enumWith

public static Schema enumWith(String... values)
Creates a Schema of ENUM type, with the given enum values. The set of values given should be unique and must contains at least one value. The ordering of values in the enum type schema would be the same as the order being passed in.

Parameters:
values - Enum values.
Returns:
A Schema of ENUM type.

enumWith

public static Schema enumWith(Iterable<String> values)
Creates a Schema of ENUM type, with the given enum values. The set of values given should be unique and must contains at least one value. The ordering of values in the enum type schema would be the same as the Iterable.iterator() order.

Parameters:
values - Enum values.
Returns:
A Schema of ENUM type.

enumWith

public static Schema enumWith(Class<Enum<?>> enumClass)
Creates a Schema of ENUM type, with values extracted from the given Enum class. The ordering of values in the enum type schema would be the same as the Enum.ordinal() order.

Parameters:
enumClass - Enum values.
Returns:
A Schema of ENUM type.

recordOf

public static Schema recordOf(String name)
Creates a RECORD Schema of the given name. The schema created doesn't carry any record fields, which makes it only useful to be used as a component schema for other schema type, where the actual schema is resolved from the top level container schema.

Parameters:
name - Name of the record.
Returns:
A Schema of RECORD type.

recordOf

public static Schema recordOf(String name,
                              Schema.Field... fields)
Creates a RECORD Schema with the given name and Fields. The ordering of the fields inside the record would be the same as the one being passed in.

Parameters:
name - Name of the record
fields - All the fields that the record contains.
Returns:
A Schema of RECORD type.

recordOf

public static Schema recordOf(String name,
                              Iterable<Schema.Field> fields)
Creates a RECORD Schema with the given name and Fields. The ordering of the fields inside the record would be the same as the Iterable.iterator() order.

Parameters:
name - Name of the record
fields - All the fields that the record contains.
Returns:
A Schema of RECORD type.

unionOf

public static Schema unionOf(Schema... schemas)
Creates a UNION Schema which represents a union of all the given schemas. The ordering of the schemas inside the union would be the same as the one being passed in.

Parameters:
schemas - All the Schemas constitutes the union.
Returns:
A Schema of UNION type.

unionOf

Creates a UNION Schema which represents a union of all the given schemas. The ordering of the schemas inside the union would be the same as the Iterable.iterator() order.

Parameters:
schemas - All the Schemas constitutes the union.
Returns:
A Schema of UNION type.

getMapSchema

public Map.Entry<Schema,Schema> getMapSchema()
Returns:
An immutable Map.Entry if this is a Type#MAP MAP schema or null otherwise. The Map.Entry#getKey() would returns the key schema, while Map.Entry#getValue() would returns the value schema.
